@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Algorithm";
}

<style>
    * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
        background-color: #f4f6fb;
    }

    .about-container {
        max-width: 1000px;
        margin: 40px auto;
        padding: 20px;
        font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
    }

    .hero-section {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
        color: white;
        padding: 60px 40px;
        border-radius: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    }

    .hero-section h1 {
        font-size: 3rem;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .hero-section p {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        max-width: 750px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .content-card {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 35px;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
        box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    }

    .content-card h2 {
        color: #2c3e50;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        font-size: 1.8rem;
    }

    .content-card p {
        color: #555;
        line-height: 1.8;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .steps-container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
        gap: 25px;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .step-card {
        background: #ffffff;
        border-radius: 14px;
        padding: 25px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
        transition: 0.3s ease;
    }

    .step-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
        box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    }

    .step-number {
        width: 45px;
        height: 45px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
        color: white;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        font-weight: bold;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    .step-card h3 {
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        color: #2c3e50;
    }

    .step-card p {
        color: #666;
        line-height: 1.6;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .code-block {
        background: #1e1e1e;
        color: #f8f8f2;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 12px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        margin-top: 20px;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .feature-list {
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .feature-item {
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        color: #555;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .feature-item strong {
        color: #2c3e50;
    }

    .cta-section {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 50px;
    }

    .cta-button {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 15px 45px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        text-decoration: none;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
        color: white;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 1rem;
        transition: 0.3s ease;
        box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4);
    }

    .cta-button:hover {
        transform: translateY(-3px);
        color: white;
        text-decoration: none;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.6);
    }
</style>


<div class="cta-section">
    <a href="http://localhost:4200/dashboard" class="cta-button">
        Open URL Shortener Application
    </a>
</div>

<div class="about-container">

    <div class="hero-section">
        <h1>URL Shortener Algorithm</h1>
        <p>
            This page explains how the URL shortening algorithm works in the application.
            The system generates short and unique links using cryptographically secure random bytes,
            converts them into readable text, and stores the mapping between the original and shortened URLs.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-card">
        <h2>How the Algorithm Works</h2>

        <p>
            The application receives a long URL from the user and generates a shorter version
            that can be easily shared. Instead of using sequential identifiers, the system creates
            random secure bytes using the built-in cryptographic random number generator.
        </p>

        <p>
            The generated bytes are converted into a Base64 string. Special symbols such as
            <strong>+</strong>, <strong>/</strong>, and <strong>=</strong> are removed to ensure the final
            URL remains clean and browser-friendly.
        </p>

        <p>
            After generating the short code, the application combines it with the base application URL
            and stores both the original and shortened URLs in the database.
        </p>
        
    </div>

    <div class="content-card">
        <h2>Algorithm Steps</h2>

        <div class="steps-container">

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <h3>User Inputs URL</h3>
                <p>
                    The user enters a long URL that should be shortened by the application.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <h3>Generate Random Bytes</h3>
                <p>
                    The algorithm generates cryptographically secure random bytes using
                    RandomNumberGenerator.Fill().
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <h3>Convert to Base64</h3>
                <p>
                    The random bytes are converted into a Base64 string representation.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                <h3>Clean Special Characters</h3>
                <p>
                    Characters that are unsuitable for URLs are removed to create a clean short code.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">5</div>
                <h3>Save URL Mapping</h3>
                <p>
                    The shortened URL and the original URL are stored together in the database.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">6</div>
                <h3>Redirect User</h3>
                <p>
                    When the short URL is opened, the system finds the original URL and redirects the user.
                </p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content-card">
        <h2>Advantages of the Algorithm</h2>

        <div class="feature-list">

            <div class="feature-item">
                <strong>Secure Generation:</strong>
                Uses cryptographically secure random number generation instead of predictable sequences.
            </div>

            <div class="feature-item">
                <strong>Fast Execution:</strong>
                The algorithm generates short URLs very quickly with minimal processing overhead.
            </div>

            <div class="feature-item">
                <strong>Unique Values:</strong>
                Random generation significantly reduces the probability of collisions.
            </div>

            <div class="feature-item">
                <strong>Readable Links:</strong>
                Removing unsupported Base64 symbols makes URLs cleaner and easier to share.
            </div>

            <div class="feature-item">
                <strong>Scalable Design:</strong>
                The algorithm can support thousands or millions of generated URLs.
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>